to the editor thomas l friedman writes of this country 's worries about iraq and the exploding deficit column aug 31 i wish that the bush administration had put as much thought into planning the iraq war and its aftermath as it did in planning the lengthy propaganda barrage that got us into the war in the first place now with a strong scent of failure in the air we can all be assured that president bush and his team are ferociously planning not success in iraq and improving the economy but their million dollar tv propaganda campaign for next year 's election to convince voters that there 's nothing to worry about garth bishop los angeles sept 1 2003

